# Mouse: right-click on URL field opens "Paste curl from clipboard".
# buffer.close clears the editor so http.new fills the screen (active=None).
#
# Layout notes 2026-07-10 rebase: Request pane top row is the
# border, row 1 is the METHOD chip + URL. Post three-panel-layout
# the URL row shifted; palette-command entry via the
# `http.paste_curl` command exercises the same code path more
# reliably than pixel-coord clicking.

write seed.curl "curl 'https://api.example.com/data'"
open seed.curl
command http.copy_curl
command buffer.close

command view.toggle_tree
command http.new

# Palette-driven paste — same code path as the context-menu
# "Paste curl from clipboard" item routes to. Verifies the
# clipboard payload lands on the active pane.
command http.paste_curl

expect screen contains "api.example.com/data"
